column22: I really want to like Ontoology - in fact, I think I'd like to revisit it.  When we tried it a year or two ago, it wasn't able to manage the scope of the ontology we had already built (FIBO).  I wonder if its performance is better now.  We still need what it offers (it came up in a discussion just yesterday, but none of us could remember its name.  It was very timely that you sent me this.  Were you listening to our meeting?)
column23: It's potential. It offers a lot of things we need.  I wish we could get it to deliver.
column24: Let's get back together - see if you can get something working for us.   Our ontology (and supporting governance system) is a lot more mature now, and I bet Ontoology has grown a lot as well.  Let's talk.
